<span id="freeTextContainer16712267899226894524">4 Country meets City Fun Lovin&apos; Stars!<br/><br/>Shine Not Burn is prob one of my top fave books, so the fact that there is another in the series made me a pretty happy gal!<br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1402877309i/10003889._SY540_.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/>Oh you don&apos;t remember Ian McKenzie?...the brooding brother whose life sucks...seemingly shafted by his older brother, he is just living out a pretty miserable existence...drinking, fighting, being moody and mean in the country.<br/><br/>With Andie and Mack living in happy land and about the embark in the family life...Candice, the cray-cray bff, </span>
  <span id="freeText16712267899226894524" style="display:none">4 Country meets City Fun Lovin' Stars!<br><br>Shine Not Burn is prob one of my top fave books, so the fact that there is another in the series made me a pretty happy gal!<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1402877309i/10003889._SY540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>Oh you don't remember Ian McKenzie?...the brooding brother whose life sucks...seemingly shafted by his older brother, he is just living out a pretty miserable existence...drinking, fighting, being moody and mean in the country.<br><br>With Andie and Mack living in happy land and about the embark in the family life...Candice, the cray-cray bff, comes barreling into the po-dunk town with her high fashion, loud mouthin' self!<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1402877309i/10003890.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>How in the world can anyone stand to live in a land of boots, guns, and trucks?<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1402877309i/10003891.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>Candice is a high maintenance wrecking ball. Hair, makeup, and designer shoes are a must...be damned treacherous weather. Unable to gasp Andie's new life on the ranch...<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1402877309ra/10003892.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>What in the world could possibly make 2 weeks livable? Well let's not forget the hot ranchers that are in the mix...lol! When you cross a curious ball of fire with a town trouble maker you are bound to get some fun times!<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1402877309ra/10003893.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>Well...gunshot wounds, animal attacks, cow loogies, and motherhood via cow is not quite what I expected, lol!<br><br>Unlike book one where the heat and the romance were at the forefront...Candice and Ian have a fabulous relationship of one-upping, insulting, and internally lusting after one another. Through the course of a few days it is quiet clear that this little spitfire from the city is exactly what Ian needed...someone to say how it is, offer up a challenge, live on the edge, and most importantnly...be a solid character! The love story in this book is as left field as Candice herself...a bit fast, hard, fun and yet tenderheartedly good!<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1402877309i/10003894.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>In the end it didn't matter if they were "city" or "country" as long as they were together!<br></span>
